	<!--
		So here's how this works:
		There are several types of populations that we want to selectively exclude creatures from.
		- Mechanimist converts, Oboroqoru worshippers, and Yd Freehold residents (these are all considered 'converts' within the game's logic)
		- Villagers, including wardens
		- Hired guards of merchants
		- Psychic thralls of legendary Seekers
		- Sultan cultists

		Villagers and converts check the ExcludeFromVillagePopulations tag, so we can apply that tag to block them from appearing in those places

		Hired guards can be prevented with the NoGuard tag. In vanilla this is only present on dream wrens, but we can extend it to anything we want

		Vanilla has no special logic to prevent thralls, but the method for selecting valid options is easily postfixable with Harmony. We use a new tag, NoThrall, to prevent monsters from appearing as thralls

		Sultan cultists are more complicated because the logic for selecting them is inline. It will need a transpiler

		The ExcludeFromDynamicEncounters tag in vanilla is unfortunately unsuitable here, because it's very general and would also prevent creatures from appearing in relevant population tables. As a result, to affect the game's functionality less, we use these instead.

		Anyway, onto the exclusions:
	-->

